				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chubert" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(502908); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=502908&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252371" alt="Chubert" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=502908)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chubert" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(502908); return false;" >Chubert</a></span> <span class="odate time_1338605738 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jun 2012 02:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1468070">
									

<p>I don't&#8230;</p>
<p>&#8230;reading this article has made me realize that I really, really don't like AWCY. I mean&#8230;</p>
<p>huh. Okay, at the time of writing my vote is a downvote, but I'm going to go back and change it to neutral. I mean, it's pretty obviously pointless bullshit, and yeah, the researcher is write, some pretentious douchebag in AWCY wrote this up to fuck with the Foundation. And the Foundation's going to spend a lot of time and power and resources analyzing the document, trying to find out what it means, even if it has no meaning&#8212;</p>
<p>-but at the end of the day, the Foundation <em>in my headcanon</em> doesn't give a single fuck. However much this document would screw with their heads, and however many people are dedicated to this thing, and however many hours of sleep are lost, the Foundation spends more resources containing a moderately anomalous SCP in one month. The Foundation has containment centers and bases of operation all around the world, information and influence in nearly all of the worlds' governments, and enough cash to fund the entire operation. Bar AWCY posing an actual goddamn threat to the world's security&#8212;my memory might be faulty, but the last time they tried to pull shit a Foundation raid busted in and shot them all-my headcanon Foundation just could not care less. Which makes these idiots just childish pranksters who think they're more clever than they really are.</p>
<p>Now, given that a. that might very well be the POINT, and that b. this is just predicated on my headcanon, I'm not downvoting.</p>
<p>EDIT: Okay, so as it turns out, there are actually SCPs created by these guys. My memory was indeed faulty. Well, even if there are SCPs, my opinion on this specific document doesn't change that much.</p>

							</div>

								
